# PR Unit Test Gate

Before creating any pull request, run the project's unit test suite and
confirm all tests pass.

## Required workflow

1. Run unit tests relevant to the changes (or the full suite when needed).
2. Verify tests complete successfully with no failures.
3. If tests fail, fix the failures or clearly report blockers.
4. Only create the PR after tests pass.

## PR requirements

- Include the exact test command(s) executed.
- Include a short summary of test results.
- Do not open a PR when unit tests are failing.

## Example

```bash
pytest
```

If the project uses another test runner, use that runner instead.
